text.tspan: Per capita non-methane volatile organic compounds emissions from
Non-methane volatile organic compounds (NMVOCs) are pollutants formed from the burning of biomass and fossil fuels.
NMVOCs can lead to the formation of other local air pollutants, such as ozone.
Data source: Hoesly et al. (2024) - Community Emissions Data System (CEDS); Population based on various sources (2024)
